        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 12:03PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 1201 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking several strong
thunderstorms over the east slopes of the Sacramento Mountains from
about Silver Lake south to Sacramento. Storms are nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sacramento, Mayhill, Silver Lake, Weed, Elk Silver, Sixteen Springs,
Hay Canyon, Cox Canyon, Dry Canyon, James Canyon, Avis, Upper Dry
Burnt Canyon, Lower Dry Burnt Canyon, Lower Sixteen Springs Canyon,
Elk Canyon, McDonald Flats, Bell Canyon, and Miller Flats.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
